        "name": "Improper Restriction of XML External Entity Reference"
      },
      "notes": [
        {
          "category": "summary",
          "text": "By sending specially crafted packets to the OPC Discovery Server at Port 4840/TCP, an attacker may be able to cause the system to access various resources chosen by the attacker.\u00a0CVE-2017-12069 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 8.2 has been calculated; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:N/A:H).",
          "title": "Vulnerability Summary"
        }
